-- TABLE-Euro-zone M3 growth slows in Dec, private loans contract
-- 
-- Wed Jan 29, 2014 04:13AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Jan 29 (Reuters) - Euro zone money supply growth slowed sharply in December, while loans to the private sector contracted at the same pace as a month earlier, the European Central Bank said on Wednesday.

The ECB gave the following percentage changes in growth,  seasonally adjusted: DECNOV   Prior   M3 annual growth rate   1.01.5   (1.5)  M3 3-month moving avg 12-mo growth  1.31.6   (1.7)   Annual total credit growth -2.0   -1.4  (-1.4)   Annual credit growth private sector-2.4   -1.6  (-1.6)-- of which loans -2.3   -2.3  (-2.3)   -- of which loans (adj. for sales   and securitisation)   -2.1   -1.8  (-1.8)  Breakdown of Loans, pct annual growth rate:   Loans to households-0.10.0   (0.1)-- consumer credit-3.0   -3.3  (-3.4)-- for home purchases  0.70.9   (0.9)   Loans to non-financial corporations-3.0   -3.8  (-3.9)  Loans to NFCs adj. for sales and   securitisation -2.9   -3.1  (-3.1)  Monthly loan flow to firms (bln euros)   -2-14   (-14)